<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="57" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1722,2035]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1758,1783]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Head red, postclypeus strongly compressed, angulated in profile with one longitudinal carina and a strongly marked lateral ridge; thorax red, pronotum with median carina, forewing either all black or apical third red and distal third black, legs black.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1722,2035]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
