<emphasis box="[359,419,1867,1891]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[443,583,1866,1890]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 30. 15 – 23" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1885,1908]" captionTargetBox="[195,1382,185,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[191,1396,185,1865]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 30. 15 – 23: Features of Ischnorhina amazonica sp. n. 15. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 16. Aedeagus, lateral view; 17. Female pygofer; 18. Paramere, lateral view; 19. Male pygofer, lateral view; 20 – 21. Dorsal habitus, showing color variation; 22 – 23. Lateral habitus, showing color variation. 24 – 30: Features of Ischnorhina hamiltoni sp. n. 24. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 25. Aedeagus, lateral view; 26. Female pygofer, lateral view; 27. Paramere, lateral view; 28. Male pygofer, lateral view; 29. Dorsal habitus; 30. Lateral habitus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215417/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
Figs 
<number box="[508,583,1866,1890]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" value="21.5" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="20.0">20–23</number>
</figureCitation>
): red, with rostrum reddish brown; compound eyes rounded, arranged transversely; vertex smooth, rectangular lacking median carina; ocelli red, closer to each other than to compound eyes; tylus rectangular, smooth, with median carina; antennae reddish brown, pedicel abundantly setose, basal body of flagellum conic without arista; postclypeus red, strongly compressed, angulated in profile with one longitudinal carina, lateral grooves slightly marked, lateral ridge present and strongly marked; rostrum extending to mesocoxae.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215417/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" targetBox="[195,1382,185,1865]" targetPageId="5">
