<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,1364]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis box="[151,234,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[255,397,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 30. 15 – 23" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1885,1908]" captionTargetBox="[195,1382,185,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[191,1396,185,1865]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 30. 15 – 23: Features of Ischnorhina amazonica sp. n. 15. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 16. Aedeagus, lateral view; 17. Female pygofer; 18. Paramere, lateral view; 19. Male pygofer, lateral view; 20 – 21. Dorsal habitus, showing color variation; 22 – 23. Lateral habitus, showing color variation. 24 – 30: Features of Ischnorhina hamiltoni sp. n. 24. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 25. Aedeagus, lateral view; 26. Female pygofer, lateral view; 27. Paramere, lateral view; 28. Male pygofer, lateral view; 29. Dorsal habitus; 30. Lateral habitus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215417/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
Figs 
<number box="[319,397,151,175]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" value="21.5" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="20.0">20–23</number>
</figureCitation>
): red; pronotum red, hexagonal, with median carina, anterior margin straight, lateralanterior margins straight, lateral posterior margin slightly sinuous, posterior margin grooved; scutellum red, with slight central concavity and horizontal grooves slightly marked; tegmina black with visible venation, apical reticulation not developed; hindwings hyaline with brownish venation, vein Cu 
<number box="[1067,1077,260,284]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" value="1.0">1</number>
thickened at base; legs reddish brown, metathoracic tibia with two lateral spines (basal spine smaller than those located in the apical crown and apical spine larger); apical crown of tibia with two rows of spines; basitarsus with one row of spines covered by sparse setae; subungueal process present, similar to claws. 
<emphasis box="[835,943,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Abdomen</emphasis>
: black. 
<emphasis box="[1036,1144,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Genitalia</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis box="[1161,1220,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Male</emphasis>
: Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[1343,1427,367,391]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 30. 15 – 23" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1885,1908]" captionTargetBox="[195,1382,185,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[191,1396,185,1865]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 30. 15 – 23: Features of Ischnorhina amazonica sp. n. 15. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 16. Aedeagus, lateral view; 17. Female pygofer; 18. Paramere, lateral view; 19. Male pygofer, lateral view; 20 – 21. Dorsal habitus, showing color variation; 22 – 23. Lateral habitus, showing color variation. 24 – 30: Features of Ischnorhina hamiltoni sp. n. 24. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 25. Aedeagus, lateral view; 26. Female pygofer, lateral view; 27. Paramere, lateral view; 28. Male pygofer, lateral view; 29. Dorsal habitus; 30. Lateral habitus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215417/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
Fig. 
<number box="[1398,1427,367,391]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
) with hooked process between anal tube and subgenital plates; subgenital plates (
<figureCitation box="[1090,1175,404,428]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 30. 15 – 23" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1885,1908]" captionTargetBox="[195,1382,185,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[191,1396,185,1865]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 30. 15 – 23: Features of Ischnorhina amazonica sp. n. 15. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 16. Aedeagus, lateral view; 17. Female pygofer; 18. Paramere, lateral view; 19. Male pygofer, lateral view; 20 – 21. Dorsal habitus, showing color variation; 22 – 23. Lateral habitus, showing color variation. 24 – 30: Features of Ischnorhina hamiltoni sp. n. 24. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 25. Aedeagus, lateral view; 26. Female pygofer, lateral view; 27. Paramere, lateral view; 28. Male pygofer, lateral view; 29. Dorsal habitus; 30. Lateral habitus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215417/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
Fig. 
<number box="[1146,1175,404,428]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
) short with digitiform apex; parameres (
<figureCitation box="[355,438,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 30. 15 – 23" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1885,1908]" captionTargetBox="[195,1382,185,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[191,1396,185,1865]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 30. 15 – 23: Features of Ischnorhina amazonica sp. n. 15. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 16. Aedeagus, lateral view; 17. Female pygofer; 18. Paramere, lateral view; 19. Male pygofer, lateral view; 20 – 21. Dorsal habitus, showing color variation; 22 – 23. Lateral habitus, showing color variation. 24 – 30: Features of Ischnorhina hamiltoni sp. n. 24. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 25. Aedeagus, lateral view; 26. Female pygofer, lateral view; 27. Paramere, lateral view; 28. Male pygofer, lateral view; 29. Dorsal habitus; 30. Lateral habitus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215417/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
Fig. 
<number box="[409,438,439,463]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
) each with one apical spine directed posteriorly, apex long and slender, dorsal process developed, rounded and prominent; aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[692,824,476,500]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 30. 15 – 23" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1885,1908]" captionTargetBox="[195,1382,185,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[191,1396,185,1865]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 30. 15 – 23: Features of Ischnorhina amazonica sp. n. 15. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 16. Aedeagus, lateral view; 17. Female pygofer; 18. Paramere, lateral view; 19. Male pygofer, lateral view; 20 – 21. Dorsal habitus, showing color variation; 22 – 23. Lateral habitus, showing color variation. 24 – 30: Features of Ischnorhina hamiltoni sp. n. 24. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 25. Aedeagus, lateral view; 26. Female pygofer, lateral view; 27. Paramere, lateral view; 28. Male pygofer, lateral view; 29. Dorsal habitus; 30. Lateral habitus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215417/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
Figs 
<number box="[752,824,476,500]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" value="15.5" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="15.0">15–16</number>
</figureCitation>
) cylindrical with two pairs of fin-like processes, the first pair located at apex and the second located medially, both inserted laterally. 
<emphasis box="[1082,1168,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1184,1270,511,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 30. 15 – 23" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1885,1908]" captionTargetBox="[195,1382,185,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[191,1396,185,1865]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 30. 15 – 23: Features of Ischnorhina amazonica sp. n. 15. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 16. Aedeagus, lateral view; 17. Female pygofer; 18. Paramere, lateral view; 19. Male pygofer, lateral view; 20 – 21. Dorsal habitus, showing color variation; 22 – 23. Lateral habitus, showing color variation. 24 – 30: Features of Ischnorhina hamiltoni sp. n. 24. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 25. Aedeagus, lateral view; 26. Female pygofer, lateral view; 27. Paramere, lateral view; 28. Male pygofer, lateral view; 29. Dorsal habitus; 30. Lateral habitus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215417/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
Fig. 
<number box="[1238,1270,511,535]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
): First valvula of ovipositor short and wide with acute apex and one basal process poorly developed, rounded, directed ventrally; second valvulae short, apical third of dorsal margin serrate, third valvulae short and wide, with long setae ventrally.
</paragraph>
